Current Details Page Redesign
Cards.Description:
What?
Redesign the user interaction and journey from current page to results page as per the wireframes and visual designs attached.

Why?
A better user interaction and design will lead to a better user experience, fewer drop-offs, and more conversions.

How is the new design better?
1.
2.
3.

How will the effectivness of the new design be measured?
A/B testing by optimost

Observations:
* the agent code can change the content (WOM, phone number, email, etc, questions) of the pre-result view.
* must be engineered in such a way to allow A/B testing by optimost and continuous release and testing (keep current implementation and feature switch new user flow)
* styles must be customisable with agent level css over-rides
* current key value pairs need to work in the new flow (currentPageHeading, defaultResultsFilterPaymentMethod, hidePreResultsFilterQuestion, overridePreResultsFilterDefault, showPreResultsFilterQuestionDefault)
* should add usefull ga metrics along the way
*

Masking of Personal data on decibel insight for signup page
Cards.Description:
Currently the default masking is switched on which masks all data in the fields across the website. However the default needs to be changed to unmask all fields and only mask the elements/fields that need masking. The list of fields that do need masking on the various pages is listed below

 

Current details page:

  • Phone number
  • Email address

 

Signup page:

  • Firstname
  • Surname
  • Date of Birth
  • Day phone number
  • Evening phone number
  • Mobile phone number
  • Email address
  • Supply address dropdown selection
  • Supply address manual address fields
  • Gas meter number
  • Elec meter number
  • Mother’s maiden name
  • Password
  • Previous address dropdown selection
  • Previous address manual address fields
  • Second previous address dropdown selection
  • Second previous address manual address fields
  • Correspondence address dropdown selection
  • Correspondence address manual address fields
  • Correspondence address firstname
  • Correspondence address surname
  • Bank account holder
  • Bank account number
  • Bank sort code
  • Account confirmation area (bank account holder, account number and sort code)

 

Confirmation page:

  • First name
  • Surname
  • Supply address
  • Email address
  • Bank account holder
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    The scope of this card is limited to the details on the signup page. Having reviewed the various fields on the signup page, with default masking switched on for decibel, the only fields that need masking are 
    - Date of Birth (friendly version )
    - Verified bank account details
    Add the data-di-mask attribute to the relavant fields that display this information.

When meter numbers are mandatory for gas and elec API accepts form if only elec meter number is submitted
Cards.Description:
Steps to reproduce:

1.select the default usage and opt for a traiff plan to switch where gas and elec meter numbers are mandatory

2.Try and fill the elec meter number but leave the gas meter number blank 

3.Fill up all the other details and click on review details and the switch should go through succesfully with out the gas meter number.

4.This is the existing behaviour for both Dual and single gas scenarios.

Expected Result: Ideally the switch should not go through and an error should get displayed saying Gas meter number must be filled.

The following tariff plans were used for testing in staging.

Dual fuel - Eon CTM collective fixed 1year june15 paperless bill

Sinlge gas - Green start energy Rate Watch Variable Paper Billing

The fix is tested and signed off.

Cards.Description:
Given that the region lookup service is unresponsive,
Then a address object with NotFound =true and MultipleAddressAvailable= false should be returned.
However if the address is found in the subsequent postcode tables (outside of the gbpostal data service) then This will continue to take precedence in cases of failure.

Display pro rata savings calculations on results table for fixed tariffs with expiry dates within 12 months
Cards.Description:
1. Given a current standard tariff, should return a personal project value for future supply traiff ending December 2016 using the pro rata calculation.

2. Given a current tariff expiring in less than 12 months, when i select future supply tariff expiring less than 12 months should display a personal projection value using the pro rata calculator.

 

Test Cases

API -Pricewatch unsubscribe resource in API
Cards.Description:
Given a pricewatch id, will send an unsubscribe command.
The api url will be in the form of
http://rest.energyhelpline.dev/pricewatch/{pricewatchid}/subscription

A PUT request to the url will always result in a OK response statuscode regardless of the status of the actual unsubscribe.

If a invalid price watch id is sent then the response will still be a OK but no command for unsubscribe will be issued.

If a valid pricewatchid is sent the response will be an OK with a unsubscribe command being issued.

If an error occurs whilst the unsubscribe command is issued errors will be reported as part of this card.

A acceptance test in Robot Framework will be implemented as part of the work that makes use of the datatemplate to update the unsubscribe resource.

The customer-home reource will have a query with rel name "price-watch-subscription" with required input value for priceWatchId.

Accessing the query resource with a valid pricewatchId will return a price-watch-subscription datatemplate resource.

Populating the datatemple and sending an update of the datatemplate will result in an unsubscribe. A 404 status code will be returned if the pricewatchid is not found. Also Any failures on the underlying infratstructure will be reported as errors. If The data template does not validate correctly, The request will result in a Bad request status code 

See attched json template files for exact details.
